fr.ecp.Group52_Project_IS1220_part1_AVEROUS_TOPUZ.Model.Network.User.Card

Class Card

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.ecp.Group52_Project_IS1220_part1_AVEROUS_TOPUZ.Model.Network.User.Card.Card
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    NoCard, Vlibre, Vmax

    public abstract class Card
extends java.lang.Object
    The Card abstract class is used to indicate the card status of a user in order to know if he has a card and what type of card he uses in that case. As a result the enumeration CardTypes defines all the possible status (NoCard, Vlibre and Vmax up to now) The abstract class is extended by a concrete class for each possible type of class he is characterized by :
    • a card number
    • a user
    • a type

    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    Pierre Averous, Nicolas Topuz
    See Also:
    User, CardTypes, NoCard, Vlibre, Vmax
